-- AutoInvite Plus - Per-slot upgrade progression (WotLK 3.3.5a).
-- The paperdoll slot-detail's upgrade list. Keyed by AIP.ItemScore archetype ->
-- numeric inventory slot id -> an ORDERED progression chain (pre-raid/heroic ->
-- ToC/early raids -> ICC BiS). Extends BiSData with per-slot organisation + iLvl +
-- an honest drop chance.
--
-- DATA HONESTY (data/BiSData.lua rule): itemIDs are web-verified 3.3.5a IDs.
-- (The old "original-vs-2022-Classic renumbering trap" warning was checked and is
-- FALSE - wowhead.com/wotlk resolves these tier/raid IDs correctly, same as native DBs.)
-- `dropChance` is a real datamined figure ONLY where one exists; otherwise nil and
-- the UI shows the qualitative source ("token", "guaranteed", "boss drop", "BoE").
-- Every row name-guarded at render. Where an archetype has no curated chain for a
-- slot, the slot-detail UI falls back to BiSData.ForArchetype + UpgradePath source
-- hints, so a slot is never blank.
--
-- Chain row: { name, itemID|nil, ilvl, boss, zone, dropChance|nil }
--   dropChance: a string like "~15%" (datamined) or nil (source text speaks instead)

local AIP = AutoInvitePlus
if not AIP then return end
AIP.GearUpgrades = AIP.GearUpgrades or {}
local GU = AIP.GearUpgrades

